RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (If A Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive A $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association)(Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMILING FELON settled off of the early pace leaving the start, tracked the decent pace from the inside and was well positioned heading into the turn, raced in the two path heading to the quarter marker, was guided back to the inside into upper stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, responded to firm urging into the final sixteenth, overtook the runner-up in deep stretch and held in a drive in the final strides to prevail. CHELSIESDANZIGLITE was sent leaving the break, was engaged by DEFENSOR FORTIS in the early stages and set a pressured pace to the half-mile marker, showed the way from the two path into the turn and was confronted nearing the quarter marker by RESERVE PROOF, shook free of that rival into the stretch and extended the lead at the furlong grounds, held foes at bay into the final sixteenth, was confronted in deep stretch by SMILING FELON and was tagged for the win in the final strides, while besting the rest. RESERVE PROOF stalked the decent early pace while outside of runners, mounted a three wide bid nearing the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch and chased CHELSIESDANZIGLITE to the furlong pole, weakened in the final stages and was clear in the end for third. DEFENSOR FORTIS was prominent away from the gate and pressed the decent early pace while inside of the pacesetter, lost a bit of ground along the turn, angled four wide into the stretch and tired in the final furlong. SMILING PREACHER chased the decent early pace while between rivals, lost position into the turn, came three wide into the stretch and was outrun in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Smiling Felon
ENTRY.OWNER: Mad Hansen Racing LLC Sandlot Racing Stables and Hansen Shirley
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside,rail rally stretch,responded,in time,held driving

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Shirley Hansen, Mad Hansen Racing & Sandlot Racing Stables

ENTRY.NAME: Chelsiesdanziglite
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,set pressured pace,shook free 3/16,tagged late,2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considere d In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRIT AND CURIOSITY was squeezed at the break and was off a step slowly, recovered in the opening furlong and tracked outside of rivals heading to the half-mile marker, gained ground while three wide along the turn, swung to the five path into upper stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker while within range, rallied into deep stretch, surged in the final strides and was up in time for the win. SPEEDING STYLE was forwardly placed away from the start, tracked the early pace then advanced to contest the pace at the half-mile marker, disputed the pace from the two path along the turn, took a narrow lead into the stretch and shook free approaching the furlong grounds, was all out into the final sixteenth, met the bid of GRIT AND CURIOSITY into deep stretch and was just missed in the final strides, while holding for second at the finish. HARBOR SKY settled outside of runners in the early stages, advanced heading to the half-mile pole and pressed the pace while three wide into the turn, disputed the moderate fractions heading to the quarter marker, lost a bit of ground to SPEEDING STYLE into the stretch and chased that rival to the furlong grounds while four wide, vied between runners into deep stretch, came in a bit tight in the final sixteenth and was outfinished by the top pair, while clear of the rest for third. PERFORMATIVE was forwardly placed away from the start and tracked the pace while inside of rivals heading to the half-mile marker, maintained a two wide path into the turn and chased between runners heading to the quarter pole, made a mild gain while two wide into the stretch, could not keep pace into the final stages and gave way. NUESTRO ENGREIDO was prominent leaving the start and disputed the decent early pace, lost position along the turn and chased into upper stretch, re-bid along the rail into mid-stretch, could not sustain that run into the final sixteenth and weakened. ARTHUR SPOONER broke alertly and vied for the early lead, raced close to the decent early pace heading to the half-mile marker, lost position along the turn and tired in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Arthur Spooner
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied early,close up 1/2,lost position turn,tired stretch

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Elm Tree Farm, LLC & Brookfield Stud

ENTRY.NAME: Speeding Style
ENTRY.OWNER: Dudzik Michael and Salvatore Raymond L
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,2p,pace turn,shook free 1/8,met late bid,just missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 98. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. One Such Race Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000, if for $14,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHOT OF A LIFETIME was forwardly placed into the first turn and stalked the moderate pace from the three path, kept close attendance to the pacesetter through the backstretch run, was roused three wide leaving the three-furlong pole and confronted LIL MIRACLE MAN at the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch, vied with HEAT N REHEAT approaching the furlong marker, turned away that rival into the final stages and drew away under a firm hand ride to prevail. HEAT N REHEAT settled just off of the early pace, came four wide into the backstretch run and tracked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, raced three wide into the far turn, slipped to the inside nearing the top of the lane and vied for the lead into upper stretch, battled with SHOT OF A LIFETIME into mid-stretch, was turned away into deep stretch and was outkicked, while besting the rest. LIL MIRACLE MAN broke alertly and assumed command away from the start, set moderate fractions while off of the rail into the backstretch run and showed the way to the half-mile marker, came under pressure from SHOT OF A LIFETIME along the far turn and was overtaken into upper stretch, chased to the furlong grounds, weakened in deep stretch and was well clear in the end for third. SUNNY SPOT settled along the inside early on while never far back, tracked the moderate pace while saving ground through the backstretch run, lost ground along the far turn and lacked a late response.

ENTRY.NAME: Shot of a Lifetime
ENTRY.OWNER: Carpenter Chris Hauck Cheryl McLean Bill Moran Elizabeth and O'Brien Patricia

ENTRY.NAME: Sunny Spot
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside,never far back,tracked inside,no late response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Kelly Stables Garcia Ken Garcia Patrick and Hirata Glenn

RACE.FOOTNOTES: EL BERRINCHES showed good speed leaving the start and dictated terms in the early stages, set a solid pace into the turn and carved out quick fractions heading to the quarter marker while off of the rail, was chased into the lane by BEAU MISCHIEF, held that rival at bay into deep stretch and kept to task in a drive to prevail at the finish. BEAU MISCHIEF was forwardly placed away from the gate, tracked the solid early pace and kept close attendance to EL BERRINCHES while in the three path, chased that rival along the turn and remained within aim while in pursuit into the stretch, could not make headway on EL BERRINCHES in the final furlong and was held at bay, while well clear of the rest. NAUGHTY NIKO chased outside of the leading pair in the early stages, maintained a four wide path into the turn and lost ground heading to the quarter marker, was not able to keep pace with the top two in the stretch and just held for third at the finish. SASQUATCH RIDE took back off of the fast early pace leaving the start, chased from the inside into the turn, swung to the four path into upper stretch, shifted five wide at the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and just missed for third at the wire. RIVER'S BEHEST tracked the fast early pace from the two path, lost ground along the turn, maintained that two wide path into the stretch, lacked a response in the final furlong and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Sasquatch Ride
ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,chsd ins turn,swung 4wd str,needed more,mssd 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: El Berrinches
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,2p turn,held runner-up at bay stretch,driving

ENTRY.NAME: Beau Mischief
ENTRY.OWNER: Blaine D Wright Racing Stable LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked 3p,close up,chased stretch,held at bay late,easy 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BY MY SIDE was sent leaving the start and contested the solid early pace while outside of SILVER MATY, dueled from the three path along the turn, shook free into the stretch, was kept to task under firm urging into the final sixteenth, felt late pressure from the runner-up and held in a drive to prevail in a good debut. ELEGANT BOY was bumped then shuffled back at the start and was off a bit slowly, recovered to track the early pace while between rivals in the second flight, improved position on the turn while three wide, was roused four wide into the stretch, finished well in the final furlong, could not reel in the winner in deep stretch and was clear of the rest for second. JOEY BRACKETS tracked the solid early pace while inside of rivals, improved position on the turn while two wide, ran evenly to mid-stretch, closed in the final furlong, could not impact the top pair in deep stretch and held safely in the end for third. CRAZY STORM was away in good order and took back off of the solid early pace, tracked four wide along the turn, improved position into the stretch and offered a mild late rally. SILVER MATY was asked for speed away from the start and was prominent early, disputed the solid early pace with BY MY SIDE and carved quick fractions into the turn, dueled inside of BY MY SIDE approaching the quarter marker, lost position heading to the furlong grounds, lacked a response in deep stretch and faded. CLICKING broke slowly and spotted the field away from the gate, raced a bit greenly in the early stages while trailing, was able to improve position into the stretch but did not threaten. SINGING N DANZING was forwardly placed in the early stages and chased the solid early pace from the inside, lost position along the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: By My Side
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,contested pace 3p,shook free 3/16,kept to task,held driving

ENTRY.NAME: Crazy Storm
ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,tracked 4 wide, turn,mild stretch rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eli gibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELEGANCE CODE settled off of the fast early pace and came two wide into the backstretch run, tracked the solid fractions to the half-mile pole, loomed three wide approaching the quarter marker and took command into the stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong grounds, was beginning to tire into deep stretch and switched to the left lead into the final sixteenth, was all out to hold off the runner-up in the final strides and lasted while fully extended to prevail at the finish. STEIN'S GIRL saved ground while unhurried in the early stages, improved position along the backstretch run, came in a bit tight entering the far turn and was taken off of the rail heading to the quarter marker, swung four wide into the stretch and gained ground at the furlong pole, closed willingly in the final sixteenth, pressured ELEGANCE CODE in the final strides and just missed for the win, while well clear of the rest. LIGHT UP settled off of the rapid early pace, maintained a two wide path into the backstretch run, was steered three wide into the far turn and improved position nearing the top of the lane, made a five wide bid into the stretch, could not keep pace with the top pair in the final stages and was outkicked, while holding clearly for third. ST HELENA tracked the quick early pace from a two wide path, was well positioned through the backstretch run while in pursuit of the dueling pacesetters, came two wide to the quarter marker, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, lacked the needed response in the final furlong and gave way. LUVAHAPPYENDING broke a step slowly, was hustled outside of rivals into the first turn and engaged with LILA AT THE BEACH to dispute solid fractions into the backstretch run, dueled through a rapid pace through the half-mile marker and into the far turn, was confronted by ELEGANCE CODE nearing the quarter marker and was overtaken by that rival into upper stretch, weakened approaching the furlong marker and faded in the final stages. LILA AT THE BEACH broke alertly and assumed command away from the start, was engaged by LUVAHAPPYENDING along the first turn and contested fast fractions with that rival into the backstretch run, carved out a fast pace heading to the half-mile pole, was overtaken midway through the far turn, dropped back into the stretch and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Lila At the Beach
ENTRY.OWNER: Smolich Andy Smolich Jim Smolich Rob and Wood Chris

ENTRY.NAME: St Helena
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace,2wd,well placed 1/2,3wd into stretch,gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 96. Allowance Purse 27000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A Claiming Price).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUNTING CARDS was well placed in the early running and stalked the decent pace to the half-mile pole, mounted a three wide bid approaching the quarter marker and vied for the lead into upper stretch, shifted to the four path at the furlong marker and was kept to task under firm urging to the final sixteenth, felt pressure from BLAZING JAMIE into deep stretch, found more in the final stages, repelled that rival's bid and edged away in the end to prove best. BLAZING JAMIE tracked the decent early pace while outside of rivals, improved position along the turn then waited for racing room at the quarter marker, continued to be blocked into upper stretch, found a seam while three wide heading to the furlong grounds, vied for the lead with COUNTING CARDS into the final sixteenth, could not match strides with the winner in deep stretch and held for second at the finish. TRINIDAD settled off of the decent early pace and trailed into the turn, was roused leaving the three-furlong pole and loomed four wide nearing the top of the stretch, raced widest into the drive and continued to gain ground approaching mid-stretch, could not muster the needed response in the final furlong, was outkicked and held clearly at the finish for third. ARTEMUS GORDON tracked the decent early pace from the second flight, lost position on the turn while two wide, angled to the three path into upper stretch and finished evenly in the drive. JEDI KNIGHT broke alertly, showed good speed away from the start and dictated terms in the early going, was engaged by his stablemate and set a pressured pace into the turn, set decent fractions from the two path along the bend, was overtaken into upper stretch, chased to the furlong marker and faded in the late stages. LUCKY LAD was hustled to be forwardly placed in the early running, raced close to the early pace and pressed inside of JEDI KNIGHT approaching the turn, lost position heading to the quarter marker, chased the leaders into the stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Artemus Gordon
ENTRY.OWNER: McCanna Tim and Silva Mary Ellen

ENTRY.NAME: Jedi Knight
ENTRY.COMMENT: good early speed,set pressured pace,overtaken 3/16,faded late

ENTRY.NAME: Trinidad
ENTRY.OWNER: Mad Hansen Racing LLC Sandlot Racing Stables and Hansen Shirley

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOB BOSS broke sharply and was well-handled racing on the outside of a trio contesting the early pace, dueled with KHAIKY'S COMMAND through the turn after OBVIOUS dropped back, put away the former before the quarter pole, opened up in the stretch and held the latter at bay under intermittent urging to the wire. OBVIOUS broke well and was hustled to the front, became the inside horse in a three way speed duel through the initial furlong, backed off the pace passing the seven-sixteenths marker, angled off the rail near the quarter pole and re-rallied to challenge MOB BOSS, ran on well down the stretch but was unable to reel in the winner. DR PESCADO came under pressure early to stay close to the early pace, became hard to place in the run down the backstretch, took an inside path through the turn, swung into the stretch three wide while still under a ride and chugged home to gain the show. MIGHTY MATT broke a step slow then made contact with EMERALD MAGIC a few steps out of the gate, began to make up ground from the three furlong pole while racing wide through the turn, was four wide turning for home and made up some ground in the stretch. EMERALD MAGIC broke out at the start, was bumped off stride after making contact with MIGHTY MATT, steadied, then was a distant last of a strung out field down the back stretch, started an extended rally while saving ground through the turn, tipped wide into the stretch and gained some ground in the late stages. KHAIKY'S COMMAND was very quick into stride and raced between three horses contesting the early pace, went on to duel with MOB BOSS through the turn, began to weaken at the five-sixteenths pole, continued on with good courage but was spent from earlier efforts. MUAY THAI (IRE) got away well, was pushed to press the pace through the early running, made a nice move through the turn to get into contention approaching the quarter pole then did not go on and struggled to keep up down the lane.

ENTRY.COMMENT: inside pace, backed off, re-rallied, chased winner home
